{
  "texts": [
    "As stated before, GAN models suffer from some difficulties that make it unfeasible of use or ineffective as per the desired requirements.",
    "Efforts are consistently applied to correct these shortfalls.",
    "Diminishing gradients slow or terminate learning, and mode collapse occurred when a generator offers diverse inputs to a single control output class, producing non-diversified examples.",
    "Divergent, repetitive, and unstable generator and discriminator training contribute to non-convergence.",
    "Some latest articles emphasizing these GAN issues stating as diminishing gradients, which stop or slow down learning, mode collapse, which happens when the generator creates highly similar instances by assigning various inputs to the same class at the output."
  ]
}